Abraxas grossulariata.label: Abraxas grossulariata
Abraxas grossulariata.description: Abraxas grossulariata is a moth of the family Geometridae, native to the Palaearctic ecozone and North America. Its distinctive speckled colouration has given it a common name of Magpie Moth. Wikipedia

Acanthobrahmaea europaea.label: Acanthobrahmaea europaea
Acanthobrahmaea europaea.description: The European Owl Moth is a lepidopteran from the family Brahmaeidae, the Brahmin moths. Wikipedia

Acherontia atropos.label: Acherontia atropos
Acherontia atropos.description: Acherontia atropos is the most widely known of the three species of Death's-head Hawk moth. Acherontia species are notorious mainly for a vaguely skull-shaped pattern on the thorax. Wikipedia

Africallagma cuneistigma.label: Africallagma cuneistigma
Africallagma cuneistigma.description: Africallagma cuneistigma is a species of damselfly in family Coenagrionidae. It is endemic to Zimbabwe. Its natural habitats are subtropical or tropical moist montane forests and rivers. It is threatened by habitat loss. Wikipedia

Aeshna isoceles.label: Aeshna isoceles
Aeshna isoceles.description: Aeshna isoceles is a small hawker dragonfly that is found in Europe, mostly around the Mediterranean, and the lowlands of North Africa. Its common name in English is Green-eyed Hawker. Wikipedia

Agriades zullichi.label: Agriades zullichi
Agriades zullichi.description: Agriades zullichi is a species of butterfly in the Lycaenidae family. It is endemic to Spain. Wikipedia

Agyrtidae.label: Agyrtidae
Agyrtidae.description: Agyrtidae or primitive carrion beetles are a small family of polyphagan beetles They are found in mostly temperate areas of the northern hemisphere and in New Zealand. They are feeding on decaying organic material. Wikipedia

Amblycera.label: Amblycera
Amblycera.description: The Amblycera are a large suborder of chewing lice, parasitic on both birds and mammals. The Amblycera are considered the most primitive suborder of lice. Wikipedia

Aglia tau.label: Aglia tau
Aglia tau.description:
The Tau Emperor is a moth of the family Saturniidae. It is found in Europe.
The wingspan is 60–84 mm. The moth flies in one generation from March to July depending on the location. Wikipedia

Amphipyra.label: Amphipyra
Amphipyra.description: Amphipyra is a genus of moths. It is the only genus remaining in the subfamily Amphipyrinae, the others having been removed, e.g., to the Hadeninae. Wikipedia

Anoplotrupes stercorosus.label: Anoplotrupes stercorosus
Anoplotrupes stercorosus.description:
Anoplotrupes stercorosus is a species of earth-boring dung beetles belonging to the family Geotrupidae subfamily Geotrupinae.
This beetle is present in the whole Europe. Wikipedia

Anax parthenope.label: Anax parthenope
Anax parthenope.description: Anax parthenope, the Lesser Emperor is a dragonfly of the family Aeshnidae. It is found in Southern Europe, north Africa and Asia. Wikipedia

Antheraea.label: Antheraea
Antheraea.description: Antheraea is a moth genus belonging to the family Saturniidae. Several species of this genus have caterpillars which produce wild silk of commercial importance. Commonly called "tussah silk", the moths are named tussah moths after the fabric. Wikipedia

Anthidium manicatum.label: Anthidium manicatum
Anthidium manicatum.description:
Anthidium manicatum, common name European wool carder bee, is a species of bee in the family Megachilidae, the leaf-cutter bees or mason bees.
They get the name 'carder' from their behaviour of scraping hair from leaves such as lamb's ears. Wikipedia

Anthicidae.label: Anthicidae
Anthicidae.description: The Anthicidae are a family of beetles that resemble ants. They are sometimes called ant-like flower beetles or ant-like beetles. The family comprises over 3,000 species in about 100 genera. Wikipedia

Anthophora plumipes.label: Anthophora plumipes
Anthophora plumipes.description:
The Hairy-Footed Flower Bee is a species of bee belonging to the family Apidae.
They are present in most of Europe, in the Near East and in North Africa. In the 20th century, the species has been introduced into the U.S. Wikipedia

Aphomia sociella.label: Aphomia sociella
Aphomia sociella.description:
The bee moth is a small moth of the family Pyralidae. It is native to Europe, but may be found synanthropically outside its original range.
The wingspan is 18–44 millimetres. Wikipedia

Apis nigrocincta.label: Apis nigrocincta
Apis nigrocincta.description:
Apis nigrocincta is a species of honey bee that inhabits the Philippine island of Mindanao as well as the Indonesian islands of Sangihe and the Celebes or Sulawesi.
The species builds nests in cavities like the closely related Apis cerana. Wikipedia

Anthrenus scrophulariae.label: Anthrenus scrophulariae
Anthrenus scrophulariae.description: Anthrenus scrophulariae, also known as the common carpet beetle, is a species of beetle found in Europe, the Near East and the Nearctic. In Europe, it is found in almost every country. Wikipedia

Apocephalus borealis.label: Apocephalus borealis
Apocephalus borealis.description: Apocephalus borealis is a species of North American parasitoid phorid fly that parasitizes bumblebees, honey bees and paper wasps. These flies are colloquially known as zombie flies and the bees they infect are colloquially known as zombees. Wikipedia

Aporia crataegi.label: Aporia crataegi
Aporia crataegi.description:
Aporia crataegi, the Black-veined White, is a large butterfly of the family Pieridae.
It is found in orchards and bushes throughout most of Europe, North America, temperate Asia, Korea and Japan. Wikipedia

Arctiidae.label: Arctiidae
Arctiidae.description: Arctiidae is a large and diverse family of moths with around 11,000 species found all over the world, including 6,000 neotropical species. Wikipedia

Archeocrypticidae.label: Archeocrypticidae
Archeocrypticidae.description: The family Archeocrypticidae is a small group of beetles with no vernacular common name, though recent authors have coined the name cryptic fungus beetles. Adults and larvae seems to be saprophagous and are often found in plant litter. Wikipedia

Apteromantis aptera.label: Apteromantis aptera
Apteromantis aptera.description:
Apteromantis aptera is a species of praying mantis endemic to the Iberian Peninsula .
This is a species of praying mantis which is endemic to the Iberian peninsula. It was first noted by Fuente in 1894. Wikipedia

Arcyptera fusca.label: Arcyptera fusca
Arcyptera fusca.description: Arcyptera fusca, the 'Large Banded Grasshopper', is a species of 'short-horned grasshoppers' belonging to the family Acrididae subfamily Gomphocerinae. Wikipedia

Asian predatory wasp.label: Asian predatory wasp
Asian predatory wasp.description: The Asian predatory wasp is a species of hornet which preys on bees. It is a little bit smaller than the European hornet. The queens may be 30 mm, the males to 24 mm; the workers are about 20 mm. It has characteristic yellow legs. Wikipedia

Astraptes fulgerator.label: Astraptes fulgerator
Astraptes fulgerator.description: The Two-barred Flasher is a cryptic species complex in the spread-wing skipper butterfly genus Astraptes. It ranges all over the Americas, from the southern USA to northern Argentina. Wikipedia

Attacus atlas.label: Attacus atlas
Attacus atlas.description: The Atlas moth is a large saturniid moth found in the tropical and subtropical forests of Southeast Asia, and is common across the Malay archipelago. Wikipedia

Aulacidae.label: Aulacidae
Aulacidae.description: The Aulacidae are a small, cosmopolitan family, with two extant genera containing some 200 known species. They are primarily endoparasitoids of wood wasps and xylophagous beetles. Wikipedia

Azure Damselfly.label: Azure Damselfly
Azure Damselfly.description: Although the term "dragonfly" is frequently used to describe the insect order Odonata, the two main suborders, Zygoptera and Anisoptera, are better designated by the use of separate English names, damselfly and dragonfly, respectively. Wikipedia

Banded Darter.label: Banded darter
Banded Darter.description: Etheostoma zonale is a small freshwater fish in the Percidae family found it the Eastern US. It is one of the 324 fish species found in Tennessee. Wikipedia

Banded Demoiselle.label: Banded Demoiselle
Banded Demoiselle.description: The Banded Demoiselle is a species of damselfly belonging to the family Calopterygidae. It is often found along slow-flowing streams and rivers. Wikipedia

Asiagomphus yayeyamensis.label: Asiagomphus yayeyamensis
Asiagomphus yayeyamensis.description: Asiagomphus yayeyamensis is a species of dragonfly in family Gomphidae. It is endemic to Japan. Wikipedia

Bembix rostrata.label: Bembix rostrata
Bembix rostrata.description: Bembix rostrata is a protected species of sand wasp native to Central Europe. The genus Bembix - of which B. rostrata is among the most distinctive species - has over 340 species worldwide and is found ... Wikipedia

Black Darter.label: Black Darter
Black Darter.description: The Black Darter or Black Meadowhawk is a dragonfly found in northern Europe, Asia, and North America. At about 30 mm long, it is Britain's smallest resident dragonfly. Wikipedia

Bibionidae.label: Bibionidae
Bibionidae.description: Bibionidae is a family of flies. Approximately 650-700 species are known worldwide. Wikipedia

Black Arches.label: Black Arches
Black Arches.description: The Black Arches or Nun Moth, Lymantria monacha is a small Palaearctic moth. Wikipedia

Blue bottle fly.label: Blue bottle fly
Blue bottle fly.description: The blue bottle fly or bottlebee is a common blow-fly found in most areas of the world and is the type species for the genus Calliphora. Wikipedia

Body louse.label: Body louse
Body louse.description: The body louse is a louse that infests humans. The condition of being infested with head lice, body lice, or pubic lice is known as pediculosis. The body louse genome sequence analysis was published in 2010. Wikipedia

Bombycidae.label: Bombycidae
Bombycidae.description: Bombycidae is a family of moths. The best-known species is Bombyx mori or silkworm, native to northern China and domesticated for millennia. Another well known species is Bombyx mandarina, also native to Asia. Wikipedia

Bombus quadricolor.label: Bombus quadricolor
Bombus quadricolor.description:
Bombus quadricolor is a species of cuckoo bumblebee.
The bumblebee is present in most of Europe except Britain, Ireland and Iceland. It is also found in Turkey. Wikipedia

Brachycera.label: Brachycera
Brachycera.description: The Brachycera are a suborder of the order Diptera. It is a major suborder consisting of around 120 families. Their most distinguishing characteristic is reduced antenna segmentation. Wikipedia

Braulidae.label: Braulidae
Braulidae.description: Braulidae, or bee lice, is a family of flies with eight species in two genera, Braula and Megabraula. These are most unusual flies, wingless and small, and barely recognizable as Diptera as they have the superficial appearance of mites or lice. Wikipedia

Brentidae.label: Brentidae
Brentidae.description: Brentidae is a cosmopolitan family of primarily xylophagous beetles also known as straight-snouted weevils. Wikipedia

Brintesia circe.label: Brintesia circe
Brintesia circe.description: The Great Banded Grayling is a butterfly of the family Nymphalidae. It is the only species belonging to the genus Brintesia. Wikipedia

Brown-tail.label: Brown-tail
Brown-tail.description: The brown-tail is a moth of the family Lymantriidae. It is distributed throughout Europe. It is found in North America only on the coast of Maine and Cape Cod where it is considered an invasive species ... Wikipedia

Broscus cephalotes.label: Broscus cephalotes
Broscus cephalotes.description: Broscus cephalotes is a species of nocturnal, coastal ground beetle found throughout most of Europe. Its habitat in Europe spans from western Europe into western Siberia. The species was introduced recently in the eastern areas of Canada. Wikipedia

Blephariceridae.label: Blephariceridae
Blephariceridae.description: Blephariceridae, commonly known as net-winged midges, are a nematoceran family in the order Diptera. Wikipedia

Byrrhoidea.label: Byrrhoidea
Byrrhoidea.description: The superfamily Byrrhoidea includes a number of beetle families, most of which are either aquatic or associated with a semi-aquatic habitat. Wikipedia

Calliphora vicina.label: Calliphora vicina
Calliphora vicina.description: Calliphora vicina is a member of the family Calliphoridae, which includes blow-flies and bottle flies. These flies are important in the field of forensic entomology. Wikipedia

Calliteara pudibunda.label: Calliteara pudibunda
Calliteara pudibunda.description:
The Pale Tussock is a moth of the Lymantriidae family. It is found in Europe and Anatolia.
The Dutch common name for the moth is named for famous butterfly and insect painter Anna Maria Sibylla Merian.
The wingspan is 40–60 mm. Wikipedia

Byturidae.label: Byturidae
Byturidae.description: Byturidae, also known as Fruitworms is a family of beetles, in the suborder Polyphaga. The larvae develop in fruits. Byturus unicolor affects species of Rubus and Geum, the larvae of Raspberry beetle raspberry plants. Wikipedia

Calopteryx haemorrhoidalis.label: Calopteryx haemorrhoidalis
Calopteryx haemorrhoidalis.description:
The Copper Demoiselle is a species of damselfly which is found in southern Europe. It is often found along streams and rivers, which are clear and rich in oxygen. The abdomen of the male shows a distinctive pink rear.
The wingspan is 60–70 mm. Wikipedia

Caloptilia azaleella.label: Caloptilia azaleella
Caloptilia azaleella.description:
The Azalea leaf miner is a moth of the Gracillariidae family. It is endemic to Japan, but has been introduced worldwide.
The wingspan is 10–11 millimetres. The moth flies from May to October depending on the location. Wikipedia

Canacidae.label: Canacidae
Canacidae.description: Canacidae, incorrectly Canaceidae, or beach flies, surf or surge flies, is a family of Diptera.There are 113 species in 12 genera. The family now includes Tethinidae as a subfamily. Wikipedia

Cane beetle.label: Cane beetle
Cane beetle.description: The cane beetle, Dermolepida albohirtum, is a native Australian beetle and a pest of the sugar cane. Wikipedia

Capniidae.label: Capniidae
Capniidae.description: The Capniidae, the small winter stoneflies, are a family of insects in the stonefly order. It constitutes one of the largest stonefly families, containing some 300 species distributed throughout the holarctic. Wikipedia

Carabus auronitens.label: Carabus auronitens
Carabus auronitens.description: Carabus auronitens is a species of beetle in family Carabidae. Wikipedia

Carabus cancellatus.label: Carabus cancellatus
Carabus cancellatus.description: Carabus cancellatus is a ground beetle common in Central- and Northern Europe and Siberia. It has also been introduced into North America. Its length is 17–32 millimetres. Wikipedia

Carabus coriaceus.label: Carabus coriaceus
Carabus coriaceus.description: Carabus coriaceus is a species of beetle widespread in Europe, where it is primarily found in deciduous forests and mixed forests. Wikipedia

Carabus glabratus.label: Carabus glabratus
Carabus glabratus.description: Carabus glabratus is a species of beetle. It is a Boreo-arctic Montane species widespread in Central Europe and Northern Europe north to the Arctic Circle. Wikipedia

Carabus granulatus.label: Carabus granulatus
Carabus granulatus.description: Carabus granulatus is a species of beetle. It is widespread in Europe and Asia and has been introduced to North America. It lives in fields, prairies and in forests. Wikipedia

Carabus nemoralis.label: Carabus nemoralis
Carabus nemoralis.description: Carabus nemoralis is a ground beetle common in central and northern Europe, as well as Iceland and the island of Newfoundland. It has also been introduced to and expanding its range in throughout North America. Wikipedia

Carabus violaceus.label: Carabus violaceus
Carabus violaceus.description: Carabus violaceus, sometimes called the violet ground beetle, or the rain beetle is a nocturnal species of a beetle, from a family Carabidae. Wikipedia

Cardinal beetle.label: Cardinal beetle
Cardinal beetle.description: The name cardinal beetle typically refers to three different species of beetle. The Red-headed or 'Common' Cardinal beetle is a red to orange beetle with, as the name suggests, a red head. It is approximately 20mm long and found throughout Britain. Wikipedia

Carniolan honey bee.label: Carniolan honey bee
Carniolan honey bee.description: The Carniolan honey bee is a subspecies of the western honey bee. The Carniolan honey bee is native to Slovenia, southern Austria, and parts of Croatia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Serbia, Hungary, Romania, and Bulgaria. Wikipedia

Carrot fly.label: Carrot fly
Carrot fly.description: The carrot fly is a pest of gardens and farms, and mainly affects the crop of carrots, but can also attack parsnips, parsley and celery. It is a member of the family Psilidae. Wikipedia

Cascoplecia.label: Cascoplecia
Cascoplecia.description: Cascoplecia, commonly known as the unicorn fly, is a monotypic genus of extinct dipteran that lived in the Early Cretaceous. Its fossil was found in the Burmese amber. Wikipedia

Cataglyphis.label: Cataglyphis
Cataglyphis.description: Cataglyphis, or desert ants, is a genus of ant in the subfamily Formicinae. Its most famous species is C. bicolor, the Sahara Desert ant, which runs on hot sand to find insects that died of heat ... Wikipedia

Ceratocanthinae.label: Ceratocanthinae
Ceratocanthinae.description:
Ceratocanthinae is a subfamily of Hybosoridae in the superfamily Scarabaeoidea. Type genus Ceratocanthus. It includes three tribes within 40 genus, and 328 species.
Synonym
Acanthoceridae Lacordaire, 1856 Wikipedia

Ceratopogonidae.label: Ceratopogonidae
Ceratopogonidae.description: Ceratopogonidae, or biting midges, are a family of small flies in the order Diptera. They are closely related to the Chironomidae, Simuliidae, and Thaumaleidae. Wikipedia

Cethosia cyane.label: Cethosia cyane
Cethosia cyane.description: The Leopard Lacewing is a species of heliconiine butterfly found from India to southern China, and Indochina. Wikipedia

Cerylonidae.label: Cerylonidae
Cerylonidae.description: Cerylonidae is a family of beetles, in the suborder Polyphaga.The Cerylonidae are a family of small to minute beetles which occur most commonly in forest litter and under bark. Wikipedia

Chalkhill Blue.label: Chalkhill Blue
Chalkhill Blue.description: The Chalkhill Blue is a butterfly in the family Lycaenidae. It is found in the Palearctic ecozone Wikipedia

Chaoboridae.label: Chaoboridae
Chaoboridae.description: Chaoboridae, commonly known as phantom midges, are a family of fairly common midges with a cosmopolitan distribution. They are closely related to Corethrellidae and Chironomidae; the adults are differentiated through peculiarities in wing venation. Wikipedia

Charaxes jasius.label: Charaxes jasius
Charaxes jasius.description: Charaxes jasius, the Two-tailed Pasha or Foxy Emperor, is a butterfly in the family Nymphalidae. It is the only European species of the genus Charaxes. Wikipedia

Cheese fly.label: Cheese fly
Cheese fly.description: Piophilidae are a family of "true flies", which is to say that they are in the order Diptera. The so-called cheese flies are the best-known members, but most species of the Piophilidae are scavengers in animal products, carrion and fungi. Wikipedia

Chiasognathus grantii.label: Chiasognathus grantii
Chiasognathus grantii.description: Chiasognathus grantii is a species of stag beetle found in Argentina and Chile. It is known as Darwin's beetle, Grant's stag beetle, or the Chilean stag beetle. Wikipedia

Chigoe flea.label: Chigoe flea
Chigoe flea.description: The chigoe flea or jigger is a parasitic arthropod found in most tropical and sub-tropical climates, not to be confused with the larval form of Trombiculidae found in more temperate climates. Wikipedia

Chloropidae.label: Chloropidae
Chloropidae.description: The Chloropidae are a family of flies commonly known as frit flies or grass flies. About 2000 described species are in over 160 genera distributed worldwide. Wikipedia

Chorthippus parallelus.label: Chorthippus parallelus
Chorthippus parallelus.description: Chorthippus parallelus, the meadow grasshopper, is a common species of grasshopper found in non-arid grasslands throughout the well vegetated areas of Europe and some adjoining areas of Asia. Wikipedia

Chrysomela populi.label: Chrysomela populi
Chrysomela populi.description: Chrysomela populi is a species of broad-shouldered leaf beetles belonging to the family Chrysomelidae, subfamily Chrysomelinae. Wikipedia

Chrysopidae.label: Chrysopidae
Chrysopidae.description: Green lacewings are insects in the large family Chrysopidae of the order Neuroptera. There are about 85 genera and 1,300–2,000 species in this widespread group. Wikipedia

Cimbicidae.label: Cimbicidae
Cimbicidae.description:
The Cimbicidae are a small family of large-bodied, often hairy sawflies, with only 130 species in six genera worldwide. Larvae are solitary herbivores.
The family is distinctive in having antennae with prominent apical clubs or knobs. Wikipedia

Cleroidea.label: Cleroidea
Cleroidea.description: Cleroidea is a small superfamily of beetles. Most of the members of the group are somewhat slender, often with fairly soft, flexible elytra, and typically hairy or scaly. Wikipedia

Cochineal.label: Cochineal
Cochineal.description: The cochineal is a scale insect in the suborder Sternorrhyncha, from which the crimson-coloured dye carmine is derived. Wikipedia

Cockchafer.label: Cockchafer
Cockchafer.description:
The cockchafer is a European beetle of the genus Melolontha, in the family Scarabaeidae.
Once abundant throughout Europe and a major pest in the periodical years of "mass flight", it had been nearly ... Wikipedia

Coenagrion.label: Coenagrion
Coenagrion.description:
Coenagrion is a genus of damselfly in family Coenagrionidae, commonly called the Eurasian Bluets. It contains the following species
Coenagrion aculeatum Yu & Bu, 2007
Coenagrion adelais Fourcroy, 1785 ... Wikipedia

Colletidae.label: Colletidae
Colletidae.description: The Colletidae are a family of bees, and are often referred to collectively as plasterer bees or polyester bees, due to the method of smoothing the walls of their nest cells with secretions applied with ... Wikipedia

Common Blue.label: Common Blue
Common Blue.description:
The Common Blue is a small butterfly in the family Lycaenidae, widespread over much of the Palaearctic and recently introduced in eastern Canada.
The larva feeds on plants from the family Leguminosae. Wikipedia

Comoro Friar.label: Comoro Friar
Comoro Friar.description: The Comoro Friar is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily. It is endemic to the Comoros, where it is only found on the island of Grand Comore. Wikipedia
